      <title>Mixed-Model Assembly Is Key to Profitability</title>
      <author>webera@bnpmedia.com (Austin Weber)</author>
      <description>
        <![CDATA[<p>
	Manufacturers today are producing a wider range of products than ever. Life cycles are shrinking and demand for customization is increasing. As a result, assembly lines must be as flexible as possible without compromising efficiency. That&rsquo;s why companies producing everything from pumps to pistols and caskets to chainsaws depend on mixed-model assembly.</p>]]>
      </description>
      <guid>http://www.assemblymag.com/articles/93387</guid>
